Sketching before a painting has always been so stressful for me because I put so much pressure on the sketch to be perfect! I’ve been using the @NotabilityApp to sketch looser and with less pressure to make life much easier and more fun! The program’s new Pencil tool just released lets you sketch with shading and it feels like drawing on paper. Making the process for me more organic with the ability for quick edits. I love being able to just jot down ideas on the go without thinking too much in Notability.  Hope you like this painting exercise and if you’re interested in trying out @notabilityapp use my code NBSTEFFI for 30 days free trial!

Testing Testing, 123! 📢I partnered with @AdobeDesign to try out the Text to Vector Graphic feature to enhance my design process in Adobe Illustrator!

–

I used this feature, powered by Adobe Firefly, as the foundation for my design. By using keywords of what I am looking for, the tool will generate vector graphics that can match my artboards. From there, I found elements from the generated designs to build on. The vectors are fully editable, so I was able to make them my own and still be hands-on with my design process.

–

I am excited to explore more, and you can try it now too in Adobe Illustrator! #adobepartner #adobefirefly #AdobeIllustrator

Create a mural composition with me! I am using @AdobeDesign’s new feature, Text to Vector Graphic in Adobe Illustrator to create a loose sketch and composition for a mural I have coming up. I use this feature to help my process instead of letting it do the work for me! 
 ✏️
It is important that I still draw and create everything myself to keep my unique style. By typing in minimal descriptions,  the Text to Vector Graphic feature will generate different vector icons and imagery for me to choose from. I rearranged leaves and flowers on the artboard to sketch out my placement, from there, I used this as a guide to recreate the design. 
 ❤️
I am looking forward to experimenting more and seeing how #AdobeFirefly can continue to assist in my creative process! #AdobeIllustrator #adobepartner
